snippet.textDisplay:
Ok so short story that made me realize I've matured in my feminism and become more secure in my life choices:

I was asking some friends for encouragement and to put more pressure on me so that I would study more. One of them replied with something along the lines of 'get a good degree, be a good girl and maybe someday a rich man will pick you and you can be happy or else you go to hell' and then followed it with a 'or male version, study hard and work hard and be wealthy and find a good wife and have babies or else you're f*cked'. A year ago, I would've probably shouted something about the disgusting attitude and how misogynistic that was and how he was actually an awful human. Instead, I don't know what made me empathize, but I knew he was going through a rough time so instead, I said that that wasn't nice of him and he should work through his problems instead of spreading toxicity, then followed it up with people being free to do what they like and that that wasn't the only path in life. Apparently, that was the right thing to say because he just confessed to going through a lot of problems and having his community put a lot of pressure and expectation on him for what he mentioned above. Turns out he was dealing with society's toxicity too. I talked him out of it eventually and it gave me a wild new perspective into how a lot of misogyny in both men and women is just them being beaten down and insecure and they just lash out about it. I'm so glad I was mature enough to open this discussion instead of lashing out at someone already hurting and reinforcing their negative views and my worst conclusions.
